{"/service/ndnp/wyu/batch_wyu_hartville_ver01/data/sn86072160/00514150473/1924020302/0053.xml":{"full_text":"SUNDAY, FEBRUARY 3, 1924\nTEAPOT OPERATIONS\n89 WELLS SUNK\nON OILjESERVE\nCrude Production Last\nYear Over Million\nBarrels.\nTeapot Dome which has leaped\nInto national prominence because\nof senatorial controversies over Its\nacquisition under lease by Harry\nSinclair interests. produced\nslightly more than 1.022.000 barrels\nof oil In 1923. As royalties the\nUnited States government received\nin excess of one-fifth of thia out\nput.\nDevelopment of the dome haa\nplayed. no small part in Casper's in\ncreased prosperity of the last year\ndue to the expenditure of millions\nin drilling and construction work.\nThere are now 89 wells in the\nfield. Sixty of these produce oil\n58 from the second Wall Creek\nsand and 2 from shal\u00ae pockets. Lo\ncated near or on top of the struc\nture are 12 gas wells, having a\ncapped-ln production from the first\nWall Creek sand, estimated to he\naround 200.000.000 cubic feet dally,\nto complete the total of 89 are 17\ndry holes.\nThe truly productive part of Tea\npot Is that which adjoins the fam\nous Salt Creek field. The very\nbest portion is that which was for\nmerly thought to separate the two\ninto entirely Individual structures.\nIn the field itself there are now\nerected seventeen 80,000-barrcl steel\nstorage tanks. The combined cap\nacity of these la therefore 1.300.000\nor enough storage to take\ncare of one year\u2019s production at\nthe present rate of Teapot output\nof oil.\nThe only stir created in Teapot\nsince the bringing In of the first\nproducer as a S2.C*?-harrel shale\npocket gusher on October 12. 1922,\nwhich now is doing about 50\nbarrels dally: was the encount\nering of production in the lenticu\nlar third Wall Creek sand Just be\nfore th\u00a9 end of 1923. This dis\ncovery was In well No. 402, SE*4\nsec. 33-39-78. Whether or not this\nsand extends throughout the field\ncan only be determined by further\ntests.\nPlans for future drilling activi\nties depend entlre\u2019y upon the out\ncome of the present investigation\nIn Washington as to the perman\nence of the lease to Sinclair. The\nMammoth Oil company which is\nthe operating organization is await\ning final decision before preparing\na program for this spring.\nService Clubs\nAre Numerous\nService clubs and organizations,\nin addition to the Chamber of Com\nmerce, play an Important part In\nthe civic life of Casper and the sum\ntotal of their endeavor constitutes\neach year a bright chapter in the\ncity\u2019s history.\nLuncheon clubs which co-operate\nIn all matters of public interest and\ninitiate many programs of their\nown arte the Rotarians, Kiwantans,\nLions and Realtors. Success has\nmarked all their activities.\nFeminine endeavors along much\nthe same lines are carried out by\nthe Women\u2019s Departmental club\nand the Business and Professional\nWomen\u2019s clubs, while, there is no\nend of other organizations which\nfunction in behalf of worthy pro\ngrams.\nOH fuel for ships means a big\nsaving; a 5,000 ton steamer run on\noil costs less thar a quarter the\ncost of a 3,000-ton vessel burning\ncoal over the same mileage.\nPencil manufacturers say the peo\nple of the United Sates pay more\n\u2019han $80,000,000 a year for pencils,\nrepresenting more than 30,000,000,-\n000 wooden pencils. 1\nNatrona Lumber Co.\nFor the Best\nLumber and\nBuilders Supplies\n251 NORTH BEECH PHONE 528\nR. S. Ellison\nIp\no K u \u00bb<-sc neiinmg company has for its\ncharge of Wyoming operations a man vitaHy interested in all ques\ntions affecting civic welfare.\nOIL WELL SUPPLY\nBUSINESS IS OVER\nTWELVE MILLIONS\nOil well supplies sold In Caspar\nlast year totalled considerably more i\nthan $12,000,000. This is not an ex\nceptlonal record since the latter half\nof the year found the drilling of new\nwells in Wyoming practically \u201cshut\ndown.\u201d\nThe supply business In this city\nrepresents an Investment of several\nmillions of dollars in real estate, of\nfice buildings and warehouses. An\nexcess of 125 men are constantly\nemployed and their combined In?\ncome f0r~1923 was around $500,000.\nIt Is probable that more that half\nof the business done covered the\nsales of oil well casing. At least\nseveral thousand cars of casing of\nvarious sizes were shipped Into Cas\nper.\nTastes Better\u2014Goes Farther\u2014Always Good\nPigeon\u2019s Fresh Roasted Coffee\n228 East Second St. Phone 623\nTelephone 1928 P. O. Box 1860\nProvident Building and\nLoan Association\n(A Casper Institution)\nSERVING THE HOME OWNER\nAuthorized Capital $5,000,000\nMONTHLY PAYMENTS required to pay a loan of\nSI,OOO in 84 Months\n$17.50\nALSO Serving the Thrifty, Insuring a High Degree of\nSafety with Large Interest Profits\nSIO.OO Deposited Each and Every Month for 96\nMonths Will, at Maturity, Net $2,000\nROOM 16 DALY BUILDING\nO. L. Walker, President A. J. Cunningham, Treas.\nC. W. Tobin, Secretary\nOH companies In some cases where\nlargo orders are made through local\ndealers, procure their materials such\nas casing, boilers, etc, by direct ship\nment from manufacturers. Just\nwhat the amount of this direct ship\nment business was for 1923 Is not\nknown, but it made* up a fair part\nof the total gross revenue.\nWith the return of prosperity for\nthe oil Industry, the fact that some\n600 wells are to be drilled In the\nSalt Creek and the growing revival\nof wildcatting, the increase In to al\nbusiness done by oil well supply\ndealers In Casper should be from GO\nto 75 per cent greater for 1924 than\nIt was in 1923.\ncaipet EJatJp crifiune\nBOOST PROSPERITY\nROCK SPRINGS MINE PAYROLL\nSUPPORTS LARGE POPULATION\nRock Springs, the financial and\nbusiness center of Southwestern\nWyoming is a thriving and growing\n<!lty of almost 10.000 energetic people.\nIt is situated in the heart of the\nlargest coal fields in the western\ncountry and on the edge of what\npromisee to be one of the biggest\noil fields in Wyoming. It is tribu\ntary to, and *s the shipping point of\nterritory extending for more than\none hundred miles both north and\n\u25a0out 3 of the railroad and thousand*\nof head of cattle and sheep and mil\nlions of pounds of wool are shipped\nfrom this point.\nThe coal interests are the largest\nat present, although they are close\nly followed by the livestock in\nterests. During the year 1923 the\nUnion Pacific Coal company alone\npaid out in Rock Springs and the\ncamps tributary to the city $4,757,-\n727 for the more than 2.000,000 tons\nof coal mined and shipped. In ad\ndition to the Union Pacific Coal com\npany there are ten other coal com\npanies operating within a few miles\nof the city and the total of their\npay rolls was mor\u00bb than $2,000,000.\nDuring the past year the mines in\nthe county were worked only sixty\nper cent of the time, or about 190\ndays, yet this short time work gave\na pay roll of mor\u00ae than half a mil\nlion monthly. The year 1924 pro\nmises to be one of the good years\nin the coal business and operators\nare preparing to Increase their work\ning time to from 260 to 380 days,\nwith the corresponding increase in\npay roll. According to authentic\nreports, there is no possibility of the\nworking out the Rock Springs coal\nfield within even the next genera\ntlon. The Union Pacific at this\ntime have tributary to its present\nmines more than 18.000,000 tons of\ncoal In reserve for future use, with\n16.000.000 tons on adjacent lands,\nand the United States government\nhas an equal amount. With this\nknowledge the people of Rock\nSprings are not worrying of the fu\nture.\nThe oil industry in this section ia\nyet the explorative stage. Four\nlarge companies have numerous rigs\nIn the field, wells have been sunk to\nthe depth of 3,000 fest, and-In some\nA Great Building Year\ni \u2014Has Just Closed---\nI\no I-.\nAnother Is\nAbout to Begin\nSEE BEN\n\u201cA Look Mean* a Lot\u201d\n1\nbi e^l;2\u00ab2 bse 2i ation have fi l ught us homesite buyers make a mistake\nho me b\u201d*Sl. gr Und ,h< Xp ,0 have\nNow Is the Time\nSecure Your Lot Immediately\nGet Your Plans Ready\nThen, You Can Start Your Foundation Early\nWe shall be pleased to show you lots In the following\nadditions which can be purchased on easy terms.\nEast Terrace Addition\nCasper View Addition\nCommunity Park\nSEE BEN REALTY CO.\nREALTORS\n201-203 MIDWEST BLDG. CASPER, WYOMING\nof these wells the largest gasserz In\nthe country have been brought In.\nThe formation is a very difficult\none to drill and progress has been\nslow and very expensive. The year\n1924 promises to be one of great\nactivity in oil circles in this sec-\nUon and without doubt some of the\nmany wells now in progress win\nreach the much sought for sands.\nFrom a financial standpoint Rock\n\u2022brings is one of the strongest in\nthe west and Its banking institutions\nare among the strongest in the\ncountry. At present there are three\nbanking Institutions In the city, two\nnational banka and one state bank.\nThe comparative growth of these in\nrtitutlons during the past ten years,\nis beat illustrated by the following\ntable;\nJanuary 1, 1914\nCgn_blned resources,__ $2,853,406.47\nCASPER\nBOTTLING WORKS\nCASPER, WYO.\nPHONE 136\nPure Fruit Flavored\nBeverages\nCombined deposits 8,253,571.91\nCombined Loans and\nDiscounts 1,104441.22\nJanuary 1.. IM4\nCombined resources $7437,t11.\u00abl\nCombined deposits 4,336.957.33\nCombined Loans and\nDiscounts 1,149444.03\nIncrease\nResources 84,384,478.14\nDeposits 4,073487.22\nLoansand Discounts.. 3.339,282.81\nThs people of Rock Springs look\nforward to the coming year with\nthe assurance that It irlll be one of\nthe best from a business standpoint\nIn the history of the city. The coal\naltuatlon is rapidly clearing up. the\npromise of activity in tho oil fields,\nthe great Improvement In the live\nstock Interests, all Indicate that\nthere Is good reason for the above\nassertion.\n255 West First Street Phone 617-W\nCasper Who